parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Engine Stalling and Check Engine Light Illumination
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling and check engine light illumination can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The engine stalls or "hiccups" while driving
the check engine light comes on and goes off
the vehicle surges or jerks
the engine misfires
the vehicle runs rough
and the fuel mileage is reduced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission problems and unintended movement can cause the vehicle to roll backwards or lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle can be left in any position and it will roll backwards
the transmission jumps out of gear
the gears stick
the low fuel light comes on
and the engine oil spot is visible under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Cracking and Oil Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel tank cracking and oil leaks can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The fuel tank cracks
the oil light comes on
the engine oil spot is visible under the hood
and the vehicle uses excessive oil.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electronic control module failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or shift into neutral while driving, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine control monitor melts
the transmission/computer module malfunctions
the crank angle sensor malfunctions
and the vehicle stalls or fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked or leaking fuel tank can cause fuel to leak, leading to a fire hazard, and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Strong odor of gasoline
fuel fumes seeping into the passenger compartment
check engine light coming on
gas gauge failure
gasoline nozzle shutting off prematurely when filling up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly repair recalled vehicles can lead to continued safety risks and potential accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Recalled vehicles not being repaired correctly
dealers refusing to repair vehicles despite recall notices
manufacturers not cooperating with repair efforts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of fuel system components, such as the fuel filter cap, can cause fuel leaks and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel filter cap failure
check engine light coming on
fuel gauge failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and erratic shifting can cause the vehicle to jerk or come to a sudden stop, leading to accidents or loss of control. Additionally, it can cause the engine to stall, leading to further safety risks.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle jerks or comes to a sudden stop
the engine revs or RPMs increase suddenly
the vehicle hesitates when taking off from a standstill
the gearshift jumps out of reverse
loud banging noises are heard while accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical issues affecting the transmission can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to erratic shifting, slipping, or complete failure, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission warning light comes on
the transmission behaves erratically
the vehicle experiences sudden loss of power
the wiring under the stick (automatic) is bare and touching.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded. In some cases, it can cause the vehicle to stall or come to a sudden stop, leading to further safety risks.
symptoms: The transmission needs to be replaced
the vehicle experiences sudden loss of power
the engine stalls or comes to a sudden stop.
